title: High Foreign Reserves
description: In 2021, Russia had foreign reserves amounting to $63.57 billion, indicating a strong financial position.

title: Low Prevalence of Severe Food Insecurity
description: In 2017, only 0.6% of Russia's population experienced severe food insecurity, one of the lowest rates globally.

title: High Educational Attainment for Doctoral Degrees
description: As of 2023, 24.38% of Russia's population aged 25 and older had attained a doctoral degree, showcasing a highly educated populace.
